01:58:49.000 --> 01:58:59.000
My first job was dealing with National Guard and reserve of affairs by the Army.

01:58:59.000 --> 01:59:08.000
And it was during that period that the Alabama battle took place.

01:59:08.000 --> 01:59:11.000
Going to the bridge and to riot.

01:59:11.000 --> 01:59:13.000
Rosalpar.

01:59:13.000 --> 01:59:18.000
The Army Operations Center was made up of not assigned persons,

01:59:18.000 --> 01:59:22.000
most of us came from volunteer, volunteer people,

01:59:22.000 --> 01:59:25.000
elsewhere, pulled together, and worked.

01:59:25.000 --> 01:59:32.000
My job was to contact the National Guard Commander on the ground

01:59:32.000 --> 01:59:40.000
and maintain communication for him with him for the Army staff.

01:59:40.000 --> 01:59:46.000
The very first night out, the chief of staff wanted to find out,

01:59:46.000 --> 01:59:52.000
okay, where were the marchers and what the Army doing protecting the Army?

01:59:52.000 --> 01:59:54.000
What are their deployment?

01:59:54.000 --> 01:59:59.000
